  "preFix": {
    "title": "Slab-Built Leaf-Shaped Jewellery Dish",
    "subtitle": "A leaf silhouette dish with incised veins and a gentle curve",
    "excerpt": "Cut an air-dry clay slab to a leaf silhouette using a real leaf as the template, incise the vein pattern with a needle tool before leather-hard, then drape over a shallow bowl to set the curve. No kiln needed.",
    "sourceNotes": "Technique derived from standard air-dry slab-building and nature-template methods.",
    "body": {
      "type": "doc",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "This jewellery dish uses a large, flat leaf as both a cutting template and a design reference. The ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "slab",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                  "attrs": {
                    "label": "slab",
                    "termId": "cmpe36s030000swv4s0l4c11n"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " is cut to match the leaf's exact silhouette, then vein lines are drawn in by ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "incising",
              "type": "text",
              "marks": [
                {
                  "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                  "attrs": {
                    "label": "incising",
                    "termId": "cmpensjxf0000q0v4ves7e4re"
                  }
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "text": " with a needle tool. Draped over a shallow bowl for drying, the dish takes on a gentle natural curve. No kiln needed. The finished piece makes an elegant tray for rings, earrings, or small items on a dressing table.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "suppliesCard",
          "attrs": {
            "tools": [
              {
                "name": "Pottery rolling pin",
                "slug": "pottery-rolling-pin",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Fettling knife",
                "slug": "fettling-knife",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Needle tool",
                "slug": "needle-tool",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Mop brush",
                "slug": "pottery-brush-mop",
                "isOptional": false
              }
            ],
            "materials": [
              {
                "name": "Air-dry clay",
                "slug": "air-dry-clay",
                "quantity": "250 g",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "One large flat leaf (eg magnolia, fatsia, bay)",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "1",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "PVA glue",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "small bottle",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Two guide sticks, 5 mm thick",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "2",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Non-stick baking paper",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "1 sheet",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Shallow household bowl or plate",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "1",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Cling film",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "enough to cover the bowl",
                "isOptional": false
              },
              {
                "name": "Acrylic paint (optional)",
                "slug": null,
                "quantity": "small amount",
                "isOptional": true
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Preparation",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Choose a leaf large enough to be useful as a dish: 15-25 cm long is ideal. Large, flat leaves with clear midrib and side veins give the best results. Wipe clean and allow to dry if damp.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Cover the shallow bowl or plate with cling film. Smooth out any wrinkles.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Knead the clay for 2 minutes until soft and smooth.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Rolling and cutting the leaf shape",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Roll the clay on baking paper using 5 mm guide sticks until the ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "slab",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "label": "slab",
                            "termId": "cmpe36s030000swv4s0l4c11n"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " is an even 5 mm thick and larger than your leaf in all directions.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Lay the leaf flat on the slab, vein-side up. Hold it gently in place. Use the fettling knife to cut around the leaf silhouette, following the exact outline of the leaf including any notches or lobes in the edge.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Remove the surrounding clay scraps. Do not remove the leaf itself yet.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Incising the veins",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "With the leaf still in place as a guide, use the needle tool to ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "incise",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "label": "incise",
                            "termId": "cmpensjxf0000q0v4ves7e4re"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " the central midrib first. Draw a continuous line from the stem end to the tip, pressing the needle tool about 1-2 mm into the clay. Use the leaf as your guide, tracing along the midrib line you can see through the leaf or feel with the needle tip.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Incise the major side veins branching off the midrib. Space them as they appear on the leaf. Use lighter pressure for the smaller secondary veins.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Remove the leaf from the clay. Check that the vein lines read clearly. Add any extra lines freehand if needed.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Draping and drying",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Lift the clay leaf carefully on its baking paper and drape it incised-side up over the cling-filmed bowl or plate. Allow the leaf shape to follow the bowl curve naturally; do not press or stretch.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Leave for 4-6 hours until ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "leather-hard",
                      "type": "text",
                      "marks": [
                        {
                          "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                          "attrs": {
                            "label": "leather-hard",
                            "termId": "cmpb7rmoo00008gv4xfq393tk"
                          }
                        }
                      ]
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ". Then lift off the former and place right-side up on fresh baking paper to complete drying. Allow 2-3 days total.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Once fully dry, lightly sand any rough edges with fine sandpaper if needed.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Finishing",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Paint with acrylics if desired. A wash of green or gold over the surface, wiped back from the incised veins, makes the lines stand out clearly.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Apply two coats of diluted PVA (1:1) over all surfaces with the mop brush. Allow 1 hour between coats. This dish is decorative; it is not waterproof for everyday wet use.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Variations",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "bulletList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Use a very large leaf (such as rhubarb or fatsia) for a larger fruit bowl or centrepiece tray.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Instead of incising veins, press the leaf vein-down into the slab before cutting the shape, combining both impression and silhouette in one step.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Drape over a more curved form to make a deeper spoon-shaped dish.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Make a matched set of three in different leaf shapes (oak, ivy, bay) for a grouped shelf display.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Hold the leaf firmly at one end while cutting the far end first. Work in short sections rather than one continuous stroke.",
                "cause": "The leaf shifted while the fettling knife was cutting",
                "problem": "The leaf shape lost its outline details while cutting"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use a steady, consistent downward pressure and follow the vein direction in one unbroken stroke. Practice on a clay offcut first.",
                "cause": "The needle was pressed at varying depths",
                "problem": "Incised lines look scratchy and uneven"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Cover the whole piece loosely for the first 8 hours to slow drying. Keep wall thickness at 5 mm even at the pointed tip.",
                "cause": "Thin section dried too fast",
                "problem": "The dish cracked where the leaf point is narrowest"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Smooth the baking paper before draping and ensure the cling film on the former is wrinkle-free. Light hand pressure at leather-hard stage can correct minor warps.",
                "cause": "The baking paper bunched under the clay on the former",
                "problem": "Draping left a slight wobble rather than a smooth curve"
              }
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
